Txt_Talk_DreamTheater_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0110_.Text:
*: Alright, then.
Don't let me stop you.

*: I should hope not!
Stay awhile and enjoy yourself!

Txt_Talk_DreamTheater_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0210_.Text: *: I do so love to watch Peony strut her stuff! Makes me feel young again!

Txt_Talk_DreamTheater_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0310_.Text: *: Hey, you do know who she is, don't you?
*: Of course you do! You'd have to have been living in a hole in the ground not to have heard of the lovely Peony!

*: You donâ€™t? Blimey!
Poor old you!
*: That young lady up on stage there is the divine and delicious Princess Peony!
*: She's the greatest dancing girl ever to grace the stage!

Txt_Talk_DreamTheater_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0410_.Text:
*: Wahey! Just look at 'er go!
Go on, my girl! (whistle)

Txt_Talk_DreamTheater_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0510_.Text:
*: Oh, Peony... My darling...
My one, my only, my world!
*: You might not think it to look at me, but I'm the lucky man that girl up there is going to marry.
*: Well, we're engaged, anyway... To tell the truth, I can't help worrying that she's, um...
*: You couldn't go and ask her quickly for me, could you?
*: Just, you know, go up and check if she still loves me. You'll do it, won't you?

*: Please!
I'm so worried, I can hardly sit still!

Txt_Talk_DreamTheater_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0610_.Text:
Hello there, darling!
Did you want something? What's that?
Engaged? Hee hee! Oh yeah, I am!
But to be honest, I've been thinking, and my career just has to come first, you know?

You wouldn't be a love and go and tell him for me, would you?
That I can't marry him, I mean.
Go on! Say you will! Pretty please! I'd be ever so grateful!
Pretty pleeease! Go on, you have to tell him for me! I just don't have the heart to do it myself!

Txt_Talk_DreamTheater_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0510_.Text:
*: So, um...what did she say?
I-If she changed her mind now, I don't think I could go on living...
*: She's still going to marry me, isn't she? ...Isn't she?

*: Sh-She is...? She is!
Oh, that's wonderful news!
I'm so happy! So, so happy!
*: She promised... Sh-She crossed her heart and hoped to die...
*: Huh? What do you mean you're not sure? Ahh, I think I see.
*: She's in the middle of a performance, isn't she? I can't expect her to answer while she's dancing.

*: It was a silly thing to ask you to do.
Sorry for being a bother...
